This paper is primarily focused on exploring the implications of numerical representation and precision on deep neural networks, which is a core topic in the field of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper also discusses the impact of these representations on computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also presents a novel technique to derive the optimal precision configuration, which could fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper's focus on improving computational efficiency could also place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
